<paragraph id="8BB198156472D737FF37FE5CFDE9091D" blockId="12.[138,772,413,1076]" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966472D737FF37FE5CFE750ABD" authorityName="Chambers &amp; Sparks &amp; Sydney &amp; Livingstone &amp; Cookson &amp; Whitworth" authorityYear="2020" box="[138,436,413,436]" class="Deltaproteobacteria" family="Myxococcaceae" genus="Pyxidicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Myxococcales" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="species" species="caerfyrddinensis">
<emphasis id="B97A44076472D737FF37FE5CFE750ABD" box="[138,436,413,436]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">Pyxidicoccus caerfyrddinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(caer.fyrdd.in.en’sis N.L. masc. adj. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966472D737FF0AFE7CFE9B0ADD" authorityName="Chambers &amp; Sparks &amp; Sydney &amp; Livingstone &amp; Cookson &amp; Whitworth" authorityYear="2020" box="[183,346,445,468]" class="Deltaproteobacteria" family="Myxococcaceae" genus="Pyxidicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Myxococcales" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="species" species="caerfyrddinensis">
<emphasis id="B97A44076472D737FF0AFE7CFE9B0ADD" box="[183,346,445,468]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">caerfyrddinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<location id="8ED1CECE6472D737FE21FE7CFDD80ADD" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03A729036472D737FF37FEB3FD8D0F3D:8ED1CECE6472D737FE21FE7CFDD80ADD" box="[412,537,445,468]" country="United Kingdom" county="Caerfyrddin" latitude="51.86" longLatPrecision="652" longitude="-4.31" municipality="Anglicized" name="Caerfyrddin" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">Caerfyrddin</location>
, reflecting its isolation from soil sampled near 
<location id="8ED1CECE6472D737FEC1FE1CFE380AFD" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03A729036472D737FF37FEB3FD8D0F3D:8ED1CECE6472D737FEC1FE1CFE380AFD" box="[380,505,477,500]" country="United Kingdom" county="Caerfyrddin" latitude="51.86" longLatPrecision="652" longitude="-4.31" municipality="Anglicized" name="Carmarthen" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">Carmarthen</location>
[the 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BD5026F6472D737FD92FE1CFD580AFD" box="[559,665,477,500]" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">Anglicized</collectingMunicipality>
name for 
<collectingCounty id="62D0E0996472D737FF37FE3CFEC8091D" box="[138,265,509,532]" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">Caerfyrddin</collectingCounty>
], 
<collectingCountry id="F319D8856472D737FEA5FE3CFE96091D" box="[280,343,509,532]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">Wales</collectingCountry>
[
<geoCoordinate id="EE3AFED26472D737FEDFFE3CFE7D091D" box="[354,444,509,532]" degrees="51.86" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301" precision="555" value="51.86">51.86 N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="EE3AFED26472D737FE7EFE3CFDD9091D" box="[451,536,509,532]" degrees="4.31" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301" precision="555" value="-4.31">4.31 W</geoCoordinate>
]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C314CB9E6472D737FF15FDDCFEC008FD" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB198156472D737FF15FDDCFE41089D" blockId="12.[138,772,413,1076]" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">
Vegetative cells are Gram-negative bacilli tapering slightly at the ends, measuring 
<quantity id="4CF635F06472D737FEC3FDFCFE1E095C" box="[382,479,573,597]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301" unit="m" value="0.75" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.7">
0.7–0.8 
<emphasis id="B97A44076472D737FE6FFDFCFE1E095C" bold="true" box="[466,479,573,597]" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">m</emphasis>
</quantity>
m 3.0–8.0 
<emphasis id="B97A44076472D737FDD5FDFCFDB4095C" bold="true" box="[616,629,573,597]" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">m</emphasis>
m in electron micrographs. Colonies exhibit swarming motility and appear pale brown on VY-2 agar (w/v 0.5% dried baker’s yeast, 0.1% CaCl 
<subScript id="178A9A506472D737FEBCFD66FECA09BF" attach="left" box="[257,267,679,694]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">2</subScript>
2H 
<subScript id="178A9A506472D737FE8DFD66FEFB09BF" attach="both" box="[304,314,679,694]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">2</subScript>
O, and 1.5% agar). Fruiting bodies are irregular spheroids, orange in color. Aerobic growth was observed at 30–40 C and at pH 6.0–9.0. Growth was unaffected by the addition of 1–3% NaCl. Hydrolyzes arginine, esculin, gelatin, 
<emphasis id="B97A44076472D737FE3FFCDCFE4E083D" box="[386,399,797,820]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">p</emphasis>
-nitrophenyl- 
<emphasis id="B97A44076472D737FDA9FCDFFDE3083C" box="[532,546,798,821]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">B</emphasis>
- 
<subScript id="178A9A506472D737FD97FCE2FDF4083A" attach="none" box="[554,565,803,819]" fontSize="7" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">D-</subScript>
galactopyranoside, and urea. Cells prey efficiently on 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966472D737FDA9FCFCFD3F085D" authority="DSM" authorityName="DSM" box="[532,766,829,852]" class="Actinobacteria" family="Microbacteriaceae" genus="Clavibacter" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Actinomycetales" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301" phylum="Actinobacteria" rank="species" species="nebraskensis">
<emphasis id="B97A44076472D737FDA9FCFCFD7F085D" box="[532,702,829,852]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">Cl. nebraskensis</emphasis>
DSM
</taxonomicName>
7483, and with low efficiency upon 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966472D737FD8CFC9CFD73087D" authority="TOP" authorityName="TOP" box="[561,690,861,884]" class="Gammaproteobacteria" family="Enterobacteriaceae" genus="Escherichia" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Enterobacteriales" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="species" species="coli">
<emphasis id="B97A44076472D737FD8CFC9CFDB4087D" box="[561,629,861,884]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">E. coli</emphasis>
TOP
</taxonomicName>
10 and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966472D737FF37FCBCFEED089D" authority="DSM" authorityName="DSM" box="[138,300,893,916]" class="Ustilaginomycetes" family="Ustilaginaceae" genus="Ustilago" kingdom="Chromista" order="Ustilaginales" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="maydis">
<emphasis id="B97A44076472D737FF37FCBCFF30089D" box="[138,241,893,916]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">U. maydis</emphasis>
<accessionNumber id="945D05F66472D737FF44FCBCFEBC089D" box="[249,381,893,916]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/DSM14603" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">DSM 14603</accessionNumber>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB198156472D737FF15FC5CFD8D0F3D" blockId="12.[138,772,413,1076]" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">
DNA 
<collectionCode id="ED1F00D06472D737FF58FC5CFEC908BD" box="[229,264,925,948]" country="0" name="Goucher College" pageId="12" pageNumber="2301">GC</collectionCode>
content is 70.2 mol%. The draft genome sequence of 
